INSERT INTO msxdb_company VALUES ('638','Mirinae Soft Co.','','0','KR','','As the only team that really made a successful transition from early home computers to modern PCs, Mirinae was the most traditional developer in the 90''s and famous for their eager commitment to the domestic gaming industry. The company name stemmed from the old, purely Korean word for the milky way (as opposed to the Sino-Korean term eunhasu, which is used in modern times), and their advertisements would often plead on the gamers'' nationalist spirit. In 1994, half of the staff left Mirinae to form Sailon Soft, but the two companies kept cooperating for many years.
INSERT INTO msxdb_company VALUES ('639','Daou','','0','KR','DAOU Infosys','A subsidiary of the Daou group. They first got known as an official distributor for some MSX/Zemmix products, and later became the country''s major publisher of 8-bit console games under the label Jaem Jaem Club. Their internal studio first concentrated on licensed titles, but in early 1993, all game development was outsourced to Open.
